{"id":246,"date":"2012-02-25T11:08:23","date_gmt":"2012-02-25T08:08:23","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/?p=246"},"modified":"2012-03-20T08:05:32","modified_gmt":"2012-03-20T05:05:32","slug":"afghanistan-winter-relief","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/afghanistan-winter-relief\/","title":{"rendered":"Afghanistan winter relief"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><a href=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2012\/02\/afghanistan-cold-winter-2012.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-247\" title=\"afghanistan-cold-winter-2012\" src=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2012\/02\/afghanistan-cold-winter-2012.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"245\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The focus of our charitable work is in Pakistan, but we can not sit idle and sleep well at night when people around the corner are freezing to death. This is exactly what is happening right now in Afghanistan. Afghanistan is experiencing one of the coldest winters in years and dozens of people have already frozen to death.\u00a0The ones who died were mostly children of internally displaced persons who live in tents and mud-huts in Kabul.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Islamic Relief has engaged its team to help the suffering people of Afghanistan. \u00a0They are providing families with vulnerable members, infants, young children and the elderly, with food and other necessary items to help them survive the winter.\u00a0You can find out more about Islamic Reliefs&#8217; activities in Afghanistan at <a href=\"http:\/\/www.irusa.org\/emergencies\/afghanistan-winter-relief\/\" target=\"_blank\">http:\/\/www.irusa.org\/emergencies\/afghanistan-winter-relief\/<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">QWP donors have already made a very small donation of $500 to help the children of Afghanistan through Islamic Relief. You can also donate at the <a href=\"http:\/\/www.irusa.org\" target=\"_blank\">Islamic Relief website<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\u00a0<!--YouTube Error: bad URL entered--><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You can get more information about the current winter crisis in Afghanistan from the following links:<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/www.irinnews.org\/report.aspx?reportid=94938\" target=\"_blank\">IRIN News<\/a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http:\/\/www.savethechildren.org\/site\/c.8rKLIXMGIpI4E\/b.7984195\/\" target=\"_blank\">Save the Children<\/a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http:\/\/www.nytimes.com\/2012\/02\/13\/world\/asia\/aid-groups-rush-to-help-afghans-in-freezing-camps.html\" target=\"_blank\">New York Times<\/a>,\u00a0<a href=\"http:\/\/afghanistan.usaid.gov\/en\/USAID\/Article\/2633\/Emergency_Winter_Aid_Distribution\" target=\"_blank\">USAID<\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The focus of our charitable work is in Pakistan, but we can not sit idle and sleep well at night [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"jetpack_post_was_ever_published":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_access":"","_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id":0,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content":false,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content":false,"footnotes":"","jetpack_publicize_message":"","jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled":true,"jetpack_social_post_already_shared":false,"jetpack_social_options":{"image_generator_settings":{"template":"highway","default_image_id":0,"enabled":false},"version":2}},"categories":[9],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-246","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-miscellaneous"],"jetpack_publicize_connections":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p4lWJl